THE draw for home venues of the 32 Premier Soccer league teams has been done and the venues have been announced. The PSL team will be based in Gauteng where teams will complete the remainder of the season in bio-bubble camp. The league is expected to start on the weekend of 8 August, with the Nedbank Cup semifinals fixtures being played first. The draw decided the home venues for each team as follows: Absa Premiership clubs: Baroka FC - Bidvest Stadium Cape Town City - Loftus Stadium AmaZulu FC - Lucas Moripe Stadium Mamelodi Sundowns - Dobsonville Stadium Orlando Pirates - Ellis Park Bidvest Wits - FNB Stadium Chippa United - Orlando Stadium Bloemfontein Celtic - Tuks Stadium SuperSport United - Bidvest Stadium Kaizer Chiefs - Orlando Stadium Highlands Park - Dobsonville Stadium Golden Arrows - Ellis Park Polokwane City - Loftus Stadium Stellenbosch FC - Tuks Stadium Black Leopards - FNB Stadium Maritzburg United - Lucas Moripe Stadium GladAfrica Championship clubs: TS Galaxy - Wits Rugby Stadium JDR Stars - Rand Stadium Steenberg United - Makhulong Stadium Mbombela United - UJ Soweto Campus Richards Bay - Tuks Rugby Stadium University of Pretoria - Joburg Stadium Tshakhuma Tsha Madzhivhandila - Sturrock Park TS Sporting - Tsakane Stadium Real Kings - Tsakane Stadium Free State Stars - Sturrock Park Jomo Cosmos - Wits Rugby Stadium Ajax Cape Town - Rand Stadium Swallows FC - Makhulong Stadium Royal Eagles - Joburg Stadium Cape Umoya United - Tuks Rugby Stadium Uthongathi FC - UJ Soweto Campus